{
  "thread_id": "first-proof-p2",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "p2-problem",
      "node_type": "question",
      "post_id": 2,
      "body_text": "Must there exist W in W(Pi, psi^{-1}) such that for all generic pi of GL_n, the u_Q-twisted Rankin-Selberg integral is finite and nonzero for all s?",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": null
    },
    {
      "id": "p2-s1",
      "node_type": "answer",
      "post_id": 201,
      "body_text": "Rankin-Selberg theory: I(s,W,V) converges for Re(s)>>0, extends to rational function of q_F^{-s}. Integrals generate L(s,Pi x pi) * C[q^s,q^{-s}].",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "p2-s2",
      "node_type": "answer",
      "post_id": 202,
      "body_text": "Finite and nonzero for all s means f(q^{-s}) has no poles/zeros on C^x, hence equals c*q^{-ks}. Fractional ideal I is free rank-1 over C[q^s,q^{-s}]; since L^{-1} is a polynomial, c*q^{-ks} lies in I. By spanning, some V realizes it.",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "p2-s3",
      "node_type": "answer",
      "post_id": 203,
      "body_text": "u_Q twist: R(u_Q)W nonzero (right translation is automorphism). GL_n-restriction lemma (BZ 1976, Thm 5.21 + Cor 5.22): nonzero W' restricts to nonzero function on diag(GL_n,1) because Kirillov model contains C_c^infty(N_n\\GL_n). So phi_Q(g) = W(diag(g,1)u_Q) is nonzero on GL_n.",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "p2-s3a",
      "node_type": "answer",
      "post_id": 2031,
      "body_text": "Fixed-W spanning lemma: for any nonzero phi in Kirillov model, integrals over V generate full fractional ideal. Proof: GL_n-equivariance of zeta integrals implies L_{R(g)phi} = L_phi for all g. Kirillov model irreducible => translates of phi span full model => L_phi = L(s, Pi x pi). PID structure on C[q^s,q^{-s}].",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 203
    },
    {
      "id": "p2-s4",
      "node_type": "answer",
      "post_id": 204,
      "body_text": "Nondegeneracy: nonzero phi_Q in Kirillov model => integrals over V span full fractional ideal (JPSS 1983). Fixed-W spanning lemma (Section 3a) closes the gap for fixed W_0.",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "p2-s5",
      "node_type": "answer",
      "post_id": 205,
      "body_text": "Choose W_0 = new vector of Pi. R(u_Q)W_0 nonzero for all Q. Casselman-Shalika formula: support of W_0 in N*T^+*K_1(p^{c(Pi)}); u_Q shift aligns conductor levels (JPSS 1981, Sec. 5).",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "p2-s6",
      "node_type": "answer",
      "post_id": 206,
      "body_text": "Conclusion: Yes. New vector W_0 is universal test vector. u_Q compensates conductor; V chosen from fractional ideal to cancel L-factor to monomial.",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "p2-c1",
      "node_type": "comment",
      "post_id": 2001,
      "body_text": "Without u_Q twist, integral degenerates for highly ramified pi: new vector of Pi misses conductor scale. The twist is the key innovation.",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 203
    }
